- Server 

./testServer name [-m]

The server will be started. If option -m is given, then a 
multicast connection is used for communication. The 
argument "name" is a symbolic name for the server.

- Client 

./testClient name1 name2 name3 ... [-m] [-C] -r -ffile

Start client and connect to the given server. 

-fxxx         File to load
-m            Use multicast connection
-C            Test image composition
-r            Number of rows for tile rendering

Keys:
ESC   exit
a     render as fast as possible
j     use jpeg compression
r     use rle compression
n     no compression
